{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Hierarchies","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Hierarchies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The Strong “call for action” on the page should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"negative","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","level":2},{"code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .default, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .negative, text: \"Delete\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .strong, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Styles","text":"Styles","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for following states disabled, pressed, hovered or normal (i.e. enabled)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Colored Surface","anchor":"Colored-Surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrom.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative 